resources.string:
This screen will have 1 clickable TextView for buying songs from Google Play Music store.

 On clicking this TextView, it will open either Google Play Music app on the device or browse to the music store on Google Play Store website. The user can then buy music from the play music store.

 First the app will try to open the Google Play Music app if it is installed on the device using:

 Intent intent = context.getPackageManager().getLaunchIntentForPackage("com.google.android.music"); startActivity(intent);

 If the app is not installed, browse to the Google Play Music website to buy music using:

 startActivity(new Intent(Intent.ACTION_VIEW, Uri.parse("https://play.google.com/store/music")));
